### Performance notes for 8GB machine
- Sakaue 2021 files (~600MB gz, ~24M rows): 45-75 min each for LDSC conversion
- T1D (2.5GB gz): 8+ hours, bottleneck is iterrows() with 33M+ entry dedup set
- Chen 2020 blood cell files (~1GB gz): 4+ hours for in-memory instrument extraction
- NEVER run concurrent heavy processes — I/O contention makes everything dramatically worse
- Consider optimizing iterrows() → vectorized writes for future runs of very large files

